-- Costco August same-store sales fall short
-- 
-- Wed Sep 5, 2007 7:07am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/05/us-costco-sales-idUSWEN078420070905

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Costco Wholesale Corp ( COST.O ) reported on Wednesday a 2 percent increase in August sales of stores open at least a year, well below analysts expectations. 

 Twelve analysts were expecting the largest U.S. warehouse club to report a rise of 5.6 percent, according to Reuters Estimates. Net sales for the four weeks ended September 2 rose 6 percent to $4.84 billion over the year-earlier period. Sales for the fiscal fourth quarter ended September 2 rose 3 percent to $20.06 billion.